Looking at the balance sheet, I can see the line item "Total Current Assets" which is exactly what I'm looking for.

For the initial value, on 2023-12-31, Total Current Assets is listed as 8000000.00.
For the end value, on 2024-01-27, Total Current Assets is listed as 9193203.41.

Current assets typically include cash, cash equivalents, accounts receivable, inventory, and other assets expected to be converted to cash or used up within one operating cycle, which is what we see in the line items above "Total Current Assets".
